---

<BaseLayout
  title="5-Day Safari: Tarangire, Serengeti, Ngorongoro | Go Kilimanjaro Treks"
  description="Five-day Tanzania safari with extended Serengeti game viewing."
  schemas={schemas}
>
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="page-hero-eyebrow">Tanzania Safari Itinerary</span>
    <h1>5-Day Safari: Tarangire, Serengeti, Ngorongoro.</h1>
    <p>Five-day Tanzania safari with extended Serengeti game viewing.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Request a Quote &#x2192;</a>
      <a href="https://wa.me/255677917500" class="btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&#x1F4AC; WhatsApp Nelson</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-white">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber-cta);margin:32px 0 12px">5 Days Northern Tanzania Safari</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">A Journey Through Tarangire, Ngorongoro &amp; Lake Natron</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Starting From USD 1,450 Per Person*</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Rates vary depending on season, accommodation type, and group size.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Safari Overview</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This 5-day Northern Tanzania safari combines classic wildlife viewing with dramatic volcanic landscapes and unique cultural experiences. From elephant-rich Tarangire to the world-famous Ngorongoro Crater and the raw beauty of Lake Natron, this itinerary offers a blend of comfort, adventure, and off-the-beaten-path exploration.</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber-cta);margin:32px 0 12px">Day 1: Tarangire National Park - Land of Giants</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Your journey begins after breakfast as you depart for Tarangire National Park, a breathtaking wilderness known for its ancient baobab trees and large elephant herds.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a full-day game drive across open savannahs and river valleys where wildlife gathers in impressive numbers. Expect sightings of elephants, lions, giraffes, zebras, buffaloes, wildebeests, and a variety of bird species.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">The Tarangire River acts as a permanent water source, attracting animals throughout the year and creating excellent game viewing opportunities.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Burunge Tented Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber-cta);margin:32px 0 12px">Day 2: Ngorongoro Crater - Natural Wildlife Sanctuary</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, journey towards the Ngorongoro Conservation Area and descend into the world-famous Ngorongoro Crater.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This UNESCO World Heritage Site is home to one of the highest concentrations of wildlife in Africa. The crater floor hosts lions, elephants, buffaloes, hippos, hyenas, flamingos, and the rare black rhino within a stunning volcanic landscape.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Enjoy a picnic lunch inside the crater surrounded by breathtaking scenery before ascending back to the rim in the afternoon.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Bougainvillea Lodge</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber-cta);margin:32px 0 12px">Day 3: Lake Natron - Land of Fire &amp; Flamingos</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After breakfast, drive towards Lake Natron, a remote and dramatic landscape located at the base of the active Ol Doinyo Lengai volcano.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">The area is known for its deep red and alkaline waters, creating one of the most important flamingo breeding grounds in the world. The journey itself is scenic, passing through rugged terrain and Maasai villages.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Upon arrival, explore the lake surroundings and enjoy the unique, untouched beauty of this volcanic region.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Lake Natron safari camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber-cta);margin:32px 0 12px">Day 4: Lake Natron Exploration - Waterfalls &amp; Flamingos</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Spend a full day discovering Lake Natron's unique ecosystem. Visit the nearby waterfalls where you can enjoy a refreshing walk and natural swimming experience.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Depending on the season, you may witness thousands of flamingos gathering along the lake shores, creating a spectacular pink horizon.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Optional guided hike with Maasai guides offers deeper cultural insight into the region's traditions and volcanic landscape.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Accommodation: Lake Natron Safari Camp</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: FB</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber-cta);margin:32px 0 12px">Day 5: Departure - Gentle Farewell</h2>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">After a relaxed breakfast, begin your journey back to Arusha or Kilimanjaro International Airport depending on your flight schedule.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">This marks the end of your safari, leaving you with unforgettable memories of Tanzania's wildlife, volcanic landscapes, and raw natural beauty.</p>
    <p style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.78;margin-bottom:14px">Board Basis: bed and breakfast.</p>
  </div>
</section>

